    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-15T16:13:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-15T16:13:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-15T06:43:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-15T06:43:00Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A strong high pressure system in the Tasman Sea continues to move east. A cold front and trough will move over SA on the weekend. Another cold front will move over the south early next week, followed by a high pressure system.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-15T16:11:07+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-16T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-15T06:41:07Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-15T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers about the Gammon Ranges, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds north to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain, most likely in the morning and afternoon. The chance of a thunderstorm, possibly severe with damaging winds, large hail and heavy rain which may lead to flash flooding west of Leigh Creek in the afternoon and evening. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending north to northeasterly in the morning then becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 17 with daytime temperatures reaching between 19 and 26.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:20am to 2:00pm, UV Index predicted to reach 4 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-05-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers in the far northeast, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm. The chance of morning fog. Light winds becoming south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 10 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching between 19 and 22.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-05-18T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-19T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-17T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-18T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Leigh Creek. Medium chance of showers in the far northeast, slight chance elsewhere. Winds southerly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching between 19 and 23.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-05-19T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-20T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-18T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-19T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds southerly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching between 19 and 23.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
